      • scan

        public static Set<Pckg> scan(JarFile jar,
                             String version)
        Builds the set of Pckg to export from the given jar file. Notice that "META-INF" directory and sub-directories are not exported.
        Parameters:
        jar - the jar file
        version - the version of the jar file. This version is used as 'exported version' for each packages.
        Returns:
        the set of packages.

      • scan

        public static Set<Pckg> scan(File jarFile)
                      throws IOException
        Builds the set of Pckg to export from the given file (must be a jar file). If the given file's name does not end with .jar, null is returned.

        This methods also try to guess the version of the jar file. If it can't be guesses, 0.0.0 is used.

        Parameters:
        jarFile - the file to scan
        Returns:
        the set of packages to be exported
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file cannot be read

      • toPackage

        private static Pckg toPackage(JarEntry entry,
                              String version)
        Transforms the give jar entry to it's java package name. The entry must be a file not a directory.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry
        version - the version
        Returns:
        the package object
